$interpreted: Ned: Father!
Sherlock: How many times have I told you? You're not to call me father!
Sherlock: Ey? A customer? Welcome, welcome!
Clark: I don't mean to be presumptuous, but I hope you can help me repair...
Sherlock: Repair something, eh? No problem, not a problem! Just a small service fee, that's all!
Clark: ......
Sherlock: What do you wish to repair? Take it out for an appraisal.
Sherlock: Ned, watch the shop for me.
Ned: Eh? Father──
Sherlock: You've come from the Mechanical Territory!? What're you up to!
Clark: No, no, no. I'm a student at the Rune Academy. Well, not currently...
Sherlock: Then tell me why do you have...THIS!
Clark: I picked her up in the Desert Kingdom. Please, help me repair her.
Sherlock: I refuse!
Clark: W-W-Why?
Sherlock: I want nothing to do with the Mechanical Territory! Now you get the hell out of here! NOW!
Clark: But if you don't fix her, she'll──
Sherlock: I don't give a rat's stinky bottom! You won't leave, is that it?
Ned: Father! What's the matter?
Clark: Please, I promise...!
Clark: Fix her and I'll leave right away. I won't cause you any trouble.
Sherlock: That's all well and good, but aren't you causing me trouble right now!?
Ned: Father, I don't know what he needs repaired, but he came all the way from the Desert Kingdom just to find you.
Ned: He was lost and nearly eaten by wild creatures...Father, won't you reconsider?
Sherlock: ...Hmph, you know nothing. Shut your mouth!
Clark: ...She's a very close friend of mine.
Clark: I'm begging you, please fix her.
Ned: Please, Father!
Sherlock: ...And if I refuse?
Clark: Please!
Ned: Please!
Sherlock: ...Fine.

Sherlock: But her design is very intricate. It may be beyond my scope of knowledge. 

I can't promise you that I can repair her back to the way she was.  No complaints!
Clark: So you'll do it!?
Sherlock: If I don't then you won't leave me the hell alone!
Sherlock: You've got to promise. As soon as she's fixed, you'll leave immediately!
Clark: ...Of course! I promise! Thank you!
Ned: Wonderful, Clark!
Clark: Ned, I owe you one. Thanks so much!
Sherlock: Hmph! Bring it in!
Clark: Should be this shop...
Merchant: Welcome, welcome! What is a fine fellow like yourself looking for?
Clark: I'm looking for 10 mechanical joints.
Merchant: This handsome fella' knows what he's doin', eh!?
Merchant: How'd you know I sell mechanical joints here? Very rare, ya know! I don't sell them to anyone, I'll tell ya!
Clark: Uh, I...
Clark: (Sherlock explicitly said I can't tell him that he sent me...these must be important parts for fixing Maria.)
Merchant: One'll cost you 1000 curren! That's 10000 in total!
Clark: Pretty expensive. But it's for Maria...
Merchant's Wife: Aren't you that fella staying at Sherlock's?
Merchant: That's you!? You're not helping Sherlock buy this, are you!?
Clark: Uh...I...
Merchant: Hmph! I won't do it! Give 'em back!
Clark: Why? I paid the money.
Merchant: It wasn't easy getting this batch in before SHerlock could. I ain't planning on sellin' 'em to him!
Clark: Sherlock sent me, yes, but I'm getting them for a friend...
Merchant: Don't you lie to me! If Sherlock's buying, it'll cost you triple! 30000 curren!
Clark: That's way too much! We made a deal!
Merchant: So you're not gonna give 'em back, is that so! I'll have to teach you a lesson then, son!
Merchant: Gosh diddly darn it! I ain't doing business today!
Clark: I'm very sorry...
Merchant's Wife: That dastardly Sherlock. He sent you on purpose, didn't he?
Merchant's Wife: Forget it. You paid, so just get going.
Clark: Thank you...
